01:22:31,448 --> 01:22:34,326
Interpol just registered a new
flight plan from Le Bourget.

1023
01:22:35,202 --> 01:22:38,455
Stay out of my way on this, Collet.

1024
01:23:06,066 --> 01:23:07,901
Did you kill Jacques Saunière?

1025
01:23:11,321 --> 01:23:13,365
Did you kill Jacques Saunière?

1026
01:23:14,324 --> 01:23:16,118
I am the messenger of God.

1027
01:23:19,997 --> 01:23:22,166
Did you kill my grandfather?

1028
01:23:25,294 --> 01:23:26,753
I am the messenger...

1029
01:23:27,421 --> 01:23:31,466
Each breath you take is a sin.

1030
01:23:32,968 --> 01:23:35,387
No shadow will be safe again.

1031
01:23:35,596 --> 01:23:40,309
For you will be hunted by angels.

1032
01:23:41,768 --> 01:23:43,729
You believe in God?

1033
01:23:44,980 --> 01:23:47,482
Your God doesn't forgive murderers.

1034
01:23:51,028 --> 01:23:52,863
He burns them.

1035
01:24:04,082 --> 01:24:05,083
Sophie.

1036
01:24:31,693 --> 01:24:33,403
The Teacher will be pleased.

1037
01:24:33,487 --> 01:24:35,781
What will you do once you have the Grail?

1038
01:24:35,864 --> 01:24:36,907
Destroy it.

1039
01:24:36,990 --> 01:24:40,661
The documents and the
sarcophagus, of course.

1040
01:24:42,329 --> 01:24:43,705
And the heir?

1041
01:24:47,501 --> 01:24:51,004
Will you exercise the final edict?
Spill his blood?

1042
01:24:51,588 --> 01:24:53,173
There will be no need.

1043
01:24:53,257 --> 01:24:58,095
Once the sarcophagus is destroyed,
DNA testing will be impossible.

1044
01:24:58,178 --> 01:25:00,889
There is no way to prove
a living bloodline.

1045
01:25:01,598 --> 01:25:03,225
But if you had to,

1046
01:25:04,851 --> 01:25:07,896
would you do as councils
have done before us?

1047
01:25:16,863 --> 01:25:18,198
Christ...

1048
01:25:22,911 --> 01:25:27,207
Christ sacrificed his life
for the betterment of humanity.

1049
01:25:30,836 --> 01:25:33,714
So, too, may be the fate of his seed.

1050
01:25:40,887 --> 01:25:42,681
I need the flight plan.

1051
01:25:42,973 --> 01:25:44,016
Ten minutes.

1052
01:25:44,975 --> 01:25:47,352
I asked you to get it for me.

1053
01:25:48,478 --> 01:25:50,397
I'm on break.

1054
01:25:51,857 --> 01:25:53,442
Come back in 10 minutes.

1055
01:25:55,444 --> 01:25:57,612
My nose! My nose!

1056
01:25:58,196 --> 01:25:59,614
The flight plan, please.

1057
01:25:59,781 --> 01:26:00,782
You asshole!

1058
01:26:14,046 --> 01:26:15,756
It's not "cross."

1059
01:26:17,007 --> 01:26:18,300
"Spear"?

1060
01:26:22,888 --> 01:26:24,431
What happened to her?

1061
01:26:25,223 --> 01:26:26,808
No one knows.

1062
01:26:27,184 --> 01:26:30,520
Mary Magdalene lived out
her days in hiding.

1063
01:26:32,314 --> 01:26:34,733
And the zealots pursued her still,

1064
01:26:35,317 --> 01:26:39,696
even in death,
trying to destroy proof of her existence.

1065
01:26:40,697 --> 01:26:43,033
But she always had her Knights.

1066
01:26:43,116 --> 01:26:45,577
Brave men sworn to defend her.

1067
01:26:45,869 --> 01:26:48,455
You see, to worship before her sarcophagus,

1068
01:26:48,955 --> 01:26:52,334
to kneel before the bones
of Mary Magdalene,

1069
01:26:52,417 --> 01:26:55,712
was to remember all those
who were robbed of their power,

1070
01:26:55,796 --> 01:26:56,797
who were oppressed.

1071
01:26:57,172 --> 01:27:01,718
Ultimately, the Priory hid her remains
and the proof of her bloodline

1072
01:27:01,802 --> 01:27:04,471
until most believed her sarcophagus,

1073
01:27:05,472 --> 01:27:07,140
the Holy Grail,

1074
01:27:08,141 --> 01:27:11,103
was finally lost in time.

1075
01:27:22,030 --> 01:27:23,031
What are you doing?

1076
01:27:23,115 --> 01:27:25,784
At the chateau, you said,
"It hides beneath the Rose."

1077
01:27:25,867 --> 01:27:27,327
No, no, no. Do be careful.

1078
01:27:27,661 --> 01:27:32,666
- In Latin, sub rosa. Literal translation.
- "Beneath the rose."

1079
01:27:46,054 --> 01:27:47,514
We need a mirror.

1080
01:27:47,722 --> 01:27:50,559
Backwards. In the style
of Leonardo himself.

1081
01:27:50,767 --> 01:27:51,893
Thank you.

1082
01:27:56,773 --> 01:28:00,735
"In London lies a knight a Pope interred

1083
01:28:00,944 --> 01:28:04,656
"His labor's fruit a Holy wrath incurred

1084
01:28:05,031 --> 01:28:07,993
"You seek the orb that ought be on his tomb

1085
01:28:08,368 --> 01:28:12,038
"It speaks of Rosy flesh and seeded womb"

1086
01:28:12,205 --> 01:28:16,168
"In London lies a knight a Pope interred"?

1087
01:28:16,376 --> 01:28:20,172
A knight whose funeral
was presided over by the Pope.

1088
01:28:20,380 --> 01:28:23,675
Of course, the Priory knights
were not just any knights.

1089
01:28:23,758 --> 01:28:24,843
Templars.

1090
01:28:24,926 --> 01:28:28,013
And there's just one place to bury
a Templar knight in London.

1091
01:28:28,096 --> 01:28:29,222
Temple Church.

1092
01:28:29,306 --> 01:28:31,475
Temple Church. If you'll
excuse me, my dear,

1093
01:28:31,558 --> 01:28:34,394
Roger and I must discuss
a change in flight plan.

1094
01:28:34,936 --> 01:28:36,313
Leigh.

1095
01:28:38,064 --> 01:28:40,442
Harboring and transporting fugitives?

1096
01:28:41,234 --> 01:28:43,778
You are already implicated enough.

1097
01:28:44,988 --> 01:28:48,575
You and I, Robert, have observed history.

1098
01:28:48,783 --> 01:28:50,577
Time has been our glass.

1099
01:28:51,578 --> 01:28:54,789
We are in history now. Living it.

1100
01:28:56,500 --> 01:28:58,126
Making it.

1101
01:28:58,835 --> 01:29:00,420
"Implicated"?

1102
01:29:00,504 --> 01:29:03,048
I am on a Grail quest.

1103
01:29:04,674 --> 01:29:06,301
Forgive me, Robert,

1104
01:29:06,384 --> 01:29:08,803
but you two may well
have given this old man

1105
01:29:08,887 --> 01:29:11,223
the greatest night of his life.

1106
01:29:13,099 --> 01:29:14,226
Thank you.

1107
01:29:16,311 --> 01:29:18,438
He's going to want more money.

1108
01:29:35,622 --> 01:29:39,751
I suppose this is a new technique
for investigations.

1109
01:29:39,918 --> 01:29:45,048
I've lost them. They flew to Switzerland.

1110
01:29:45,298 --> 01:29:47,509
No extradition.

1111
01:29:50,262 --> 01:29:56,560
The controller filed charges.
Ari was on dispatch. He called me.

1112
01:30:00,647 --> 01:30:03,733
What's going on, Bezu?

1113
01:30:06,736 --> 01:30:09,614
You know that I am Opus Dei?

1114
01:30:09,990 --> 01:30:11,533
Yes.

1115
01:30:16,830 --> 01:30:20,333
A bishop of my order called me.

1116
01:30:20,667 --> 01:30:22,794
He said a killer came to him in confession.

1117
01:30:22,961 --> 01:30:25,714
His name was Robert Langdon.

1118
01:30:26,881 --> 01:30:30,010
He said I couldn't imagine
the evil in this man's heart.

1119
01:30:30,176 --> 01:30:32,929
That he would keep killing.

1120
01:30:33,305 --> 01:30:35,765
He said I had to stop him.

1121
01:30:37,809 --> 01:30:41,646
The bishop broke his vows to tell me this.

1122
01:30:41,813 --> 01:30:45,233
He charged me to stop Robert Langdon.

1123
01:30:48,194 --> 01:30:52,949
Tell me, Collet, who have I failed?

1124
01:30:53,742 --> 01:30:55,535
The bishop?

1125
01:30:56,870 --> 01:30:58,955
God himself?

1126
01:31:07,589 --> 01:31:10,717
They've changed their
flight plan to London.

1127
01:31:39,412 --> 01:31:43,124
I have them, tower.
Relay Hawker to land and hold on tarmac.

1128
01:32:40,432 --> 01:32:42,642
- Secure the area!
- Wider!

1129
01:32:42,809 --> 01:32:44,936
- Armed police!
- You two, round the back!

1130
01:32:45,311 --> 01:32:48,481
Armed police! Put your hands in the air!

1131
01:32:48,690 --> 01:32:50,483
- Three men up!
- Ready!

1132
01:32:50,567 --> 01:32:52,861
Put your hands in the air! Do it now!

1133
01:32:53,653 --> 01:32:56,030
I'm afraid that's easier said than done
in my case.

1134
01:32:58,116 --> 01:32:59,409
Good morning.

1135
01:32:59,492 --> 01:33:02,579
Did that old cannabis charge
finally catch up with me?

1136
01:33:02,662 --> 01:33:05,498
Sir, the French police say
you're transporting fugitives,

1137
01:33:05,582 --> 01:33:07,333
and you may have a hostage onboard.

1138
01:33:07,417 --> 01:33:08,877
I'm to take you all into custody.

1139
01:33:08,960 --> 01:33:11,463
Sadly, I have an important
medical appointment

1140
01:33:11,546 --> 01:33:12,756
which I can't afford to miss.

1141
01:33:12,839 --> 01:33:14,048
I'll fetch the car, sir.

1142
01:33:14,132 --> 01:33:16,968
This is serious, sir.
The French police are on their way. Stop!

1143
01:33:17,677 --> 01:33:20,847
Inspector, I can't afford the time
to indulge your games.

1144
01:33:20,930 --> 01:33:22,307
I'm late and I'm leaving.

1145
01:33:22,390 --> 01:33:24,434
If it's so important for you to stop us,

1146
01:33:24,517 --> 01:33:26,728
then you're just going to have to shoot us.

1147
01:33:27,520 --> 01:33:28,938
You can start with him.

1148
01:33:34,235 --> 01:33:35,612
Search the plane.

1149
01:33:36,321 --> 01:33:37,530
All right.

1150
01:33:49,751 --> 01:33:51,419
I could run them over.

1151
01:33:56,883 --> 01:33:57,884
Bad tip.

1152
01:33:59,844 --> 01:34:01,221
Let him go.

1153
01:34:05,809 --> 01:34:08,186
The French cannot be trusted.

1154
01:34:16,945 --> 01:34:17,987
Everyone comfy?

1155
01:34:20,448 --> 01:34:21,491
Biscuits?

1156
01:34:21,991 --> 01:34:23,451
They didn't notice anything?

1157
01:34:24,077 --> 01:34:28,248
Well, people rarely notice things right
in front of their eyes, don't you find?

1158
01:34:42,470 --> 01:34:45,056
Do you have the bonds, bishop?

1159
01:34:45,265 --> 01:34:46,516
Yes, I do, Teacher.

1160
01:34:46,683 --> 01:34:50,019
I have chosen an Opus Dei
residence for the exchange.

1161
01:34:50,186 --> 01:34:51,646
I am honored.

1162
01:34:51,896 --> 01:34:56,734
By the time you get to London,
I will have the Grail.

1163
01:35:02,115 --> 01:35:06,953
Remember, if we are discovered by
the Vatican, we are excommunicated.

1164
01:35:07,036 --> 01:35:10,039
- So should anything go wrong...
- Yes, I know, I know.

1165
01:35:11,457 --> 01:35:13,126
This council does not exist.

1166
01:35:14,127 --> 01:35:15,837
As it never has.

1167
01:35:18,715 --> 01:35:22,468
Old friend. Heaven protect you.

1168
01:35:29,976 --> 01:35:31,936
Keep an eye out for the police.

1169
01:35:45,074 --> 01:35:47,827
I must say, Robert, I'm quite impressed

1170
01:35:47,911 --> 01:35:51,164
by the way you withstood
my little airplane.

1171
01:35:52,832 --> 01:35:54,459
Did he never tell you?

1172
01:35:54,542 --> 01:35:57,962
When he was a boy,
young Robert fell into a well.

1173
01:35:58,046 --> 01:35:59,797
How old were you?

1174
01:35:59,881 --> 01:36:01,007
Seven.

1175
01:36:03,718 --> 01:36:07,096
Treading water all night long,
screaming his lungs out

1176
01:36:07,180 --> 01:36:09,098
to the echoes screaming back.

1177
01:36:09,182 --> 01:36:11,726
When they found him, he
was nearly catatonic.

1178
01:36:11,935 --> 01:36:13,019
Help!

1179
01:36:14,062 --> 01:36:15,521
It was a long time ago.

1180
01:36:15,605 --> 01:36:17,482
Now, now, Robert.

1181
01:36:17,565 --> 01:36:21,861
You, above all people, shouldn't be one
to dismiss the influence of the past.

1182
01:36:27,575 --> 01:36:31,788
Tell me, why has the Priory kept
the Grail location secret all these years?

1183
01:36:31,871 --> 01:36:32,872
I don't know.

1184
01:36:33,414 --> 01:36:36,167
Some say the Priory wait
for the heir to reveal himself,

1185
01:36:36,250 --> 01:36:38,044
which is especially odd

1186
01:36:38,211 --> 01:36:41,547
since legend suggests
he may not know his own true identity.

1187
01:36:49,555 --> 01:36:50,556
Hello?

1188
01:36:51,349 --> 01:36:53,977
Why do they make them so scary?

1189
01:36:59,607 --> 01:37:00,733
It's cold.

1190
01:37:00,900 --> 01:37:04,237
"In London lies a knight a Pope interred."

1191
01:37:13,538 --> 01:37:16,916
So which tomb has an orb?

1192
01:37:19,252 --> 01:37:22,630
Two wear tunics over their armor

1193
01:37:22,714 --> 01:37:25,842
and two have full-length robes.

1194
01:37:26,926 --> 01:37:28,636
Two are grasping swords.

1195
01:37:29,095 --> 01:37:32,724
And one... Two are praying.

1196
01:37:34,684 --> 01:37:36,769
This one has his arms at his sides.

1197
01:37:36,853 --> 01:37:40,523
And this poor fellow
has almost disappeared entirely.

1198
01:37:40,732 --> 01:37:45,445
I don't see any orb that
ought be on a tomb.

1199
01:37:46,320 --> 01:37:49,198
"Ought be on his tomb."
Are we looking for a missing orb?

1200
01:37:49,282 --> 01:37:51,117
Maybe. Over here, see.

1201
01:37:56,164 --> 01:37:57,874
These aren't tombs.

1202
01:37:57,957 --> 01:38:00,418
- What? Yes, of course they are.
- No.

1203
01:38:00,501 --> 01:38:02,628
- They're effigies.
- What?

1204
01:38:02,712 --> 01:38:04,797
Not tombs. There's no bodies here.

1205
01:38:04,964 --> 01:38:06,424
This place is wrong.

1206
01:38:08,468 --> 01:38:11,804
Can we go now? We should go.

1207
01:38:14,974 --> 01:38:16,476
Sophie! No!

1208
01:38:18,436 --> 01:38:19,854
Where is the keystone?

1209
01:38:20,980 --> 01:38:22,231
Do not test me!

1210
01:38:22,315 --> 01:38:23,608
- Let her go!
- Don't you hurt her.

1211
01:38:23,691 --> 01:38:25,777
- Give me the keystone! Give it to me!
- Can you stop that?

1212
01:38:25,860 --> 01:38:27,612
Here! Here! Here it is! Here it is.

1213
01:38:27,695 --> 01:38:30,948
Just let her go, and you and I can...
We'll come to some agreement.

1214
01:38:32,200 --> 01:38:33,659
Remy.

1215
01:38:36,996 --> 01:38:39,540
Remy. No, no, no. No, put it away.

1216
01:38:40,833 --> 01:38:43,169
Put it away. They're too close together.
You don't have a clear shot.

1217
01:38:44,295 --> 01:38:46,672
- Yes, I do.
- Stop that. What do you think you're doing?

1218
01:38:48,925 --> 01:38:53,304
Thank you, Professor.
For a moment, this was getting complicated.

1219
01:38:53,387 --> 01:38:55,473
This is absurd. For God's sake, man!

1220
01:38:58,935 --> 01:39:01,145
That was satisfying.

1221
01:39:01,229 --> 01:39:03,106
I'm glad this bullshit is over.

1222
01:39:06,359 --> 01:39:08,069
Throw Teabing in the trunk.

1223
01:39:08,277 --> 01:39:09,529
What?

1224
01:39:14,951 --> 01:39:16,494
Here. You okay?

1225
01:39:22,375 --> 01:39:23,376
Sorry.

1226
01:40:04,417 --> 01:40:06,210
I don't think he's following.

1227
01:40:14,427 --> 01:40:18,306
They won't kill Leigh
until they find the Grail.

1228
01:40:20,433 --> 01:40:23,644
- So we have to find it before they do.
- I have to get to a library, fast.

1229
01:40:31,611 --> 01:40:35,948
He once whined to me about
the wasted space of so large a trunk.

1230
01:40:36,991 --> 01:40:39,118
Let's see if he complains so now.

1231
01:40:40,203 --> 01:40:42,121
Are you the Teacher?

1232
01:40:45,374 --> 01:40:46,417
I am.

1233
01:40:48,211 --> 01:40:52,715
Superbly done. You've
been of great service.

1234
01:40:56,219 --> 01:40:59,222
The cryptex has yet to be opened.
I can still serve.

1235
01:40:59,305 --> 01:41:01,474
You've done enough.

1236
01:41:04,560 --> 01:41:08,231
We cannot let ego deter us from our goal.

1237
01:41:09,440 --> 01:41:11,400
I understand.

1238
01:41:12,401 --> 01:41:13,527
Good.

1239
01:41:16,739 --> 01:41:21,619
Wait here, at this house of Opus Dei,
and you will be rewarded.

1240
01:41:21,702 --> 01:41:23,913
I will dispose of the old man.

1241
01:41:25,081 --> 01:41:26,707
Bless you, Silas.

1242
01:41:28,751 --> 01:41:30,002
Teacher.

1243
01:41:38,177 --> 01:41:39,929
Christ be with you.

1244
01:41:42,682 --> 01:41:47,520
We're at least a half-hour
to Chelsea Library.

1245
01:41:48,104 --> 01:41:50,147
If we're gonna help Leigh, that's too long.

1246
01:42:01,867 --> 01:42:03,369
Where are you going?

1247
01:42:03,452 --> 01:42:05,579
Getting you a library card.

1248
01:42:09,208 --> 01:42:11,335
Excuse me. May I sit next to you?

1249
01:42:11,419 --> 01:42:13,921
- Yeah, sure.
- Thank you.

1250
01:42:22,471 --> 01:42:23,764
That's great.

1251
01:42:24,724 --> 01:42:26,892
Didn't say you had a boyfriend.

1252
01:42:29,603 --> 01:42:30,896
Thanks.

1253
01:42:31,564 --> 01:42:33,899
Let's see if we can access
the database on this.

1254
01:42:35,234 --> 01:42:38,571
"In London lies a knight a Pope interred."

1255
01:42:38,654 --> 01:42:40,406
Compounding keywords.

1256
01:42:40,614 --> 01:42:43,492
Knight, Pope, Grail.

1257
01:42:44,118 --> 01:42:48,122
Your precious treasure
was almost lost, and with it, my fortune.

1258
01:42:52,543 --> 01:42:54,795
Can you believe how well I did?

1259
01:42:56,380 --> 01:42:58,507
I even convinced the monk.

1260
01:42:59,383 --> 01:43:01,302
I should be in theater.

1261
01:43:08,017 --> 01:43:11,020
A toast to our success, Teacher.

1262
01:43:11,103 --> 01:43:13,522
The end of the journey is near.

1263
01:43:16,067 --> 01:43:19,362
Your identity shall go
with me to the grave.

1264
01:43:24,784 --> 01:43:28,454
There's your problem, mate.
It's your basic linguistic coincidence.

1265
01:43:28,871 --> 01:43:31,123
See, keywords keep coming up
with the writings

1266
01:43:31,207 --> 01:43:34,251
of some bloke named Alexander Pope.

1267
01:43:34,335 --> 01:43:35,586
"A. Pope."

1268
01:43:37,213 --> 01:43:38,964
Your grandfather was a genius.

1269
01:43:43,886 --> 01:43:44,929
Come on.

1270
01:44:19,588 --> 01:44:21,424
Emergency. Which service do you require?

1271
01:44:21,507 --> 01:44:26,595
I know the location of two murderers
wanted by French police.

1272
01:44:30,516 --> 01:44:32,726
We've just had a 999 call.

1273
01:44:32,810 --> 01:44:35,271
Triangulation leads back to Docklands.

1274
01:44:35,354 --> 01:44:37,523
Caller was male. Claimed your two murderers

