02:07:33,356 --> 02:07:35,024
Never look for them, Sophie.

1535
02:07:35,274 --> 02:07:36,484
Promise me.

1536
02:07:37,944 --> 02:07:39,070
Swear it!

1537
02:07:39,779 --> 02:07:40,905
Swear it to me!

1538
02:07:51,582 --> 02:07:53,543
I kept my promise.

1539
02:07:57,171 --> 02:07:59,465
The next week he sent
me to boarding school.

1540
02:08:01,676 --> 02:08:04,637
One weekend, I came home unexpectedly.

1541
02:08:06,264 --> 02:08:08,349
And what I saw my grandfather doing...

1542
02:08:09,976 --> 02:08:11,602
Some ritual.

1543
02:08:13,604 --> 02:08:15,189
I was so frightened.

1544
02:08:19,861 --> 02:08:22,029
We hardly ever spoke again.

1545
02:08:25,658 --> 02:08:27,285
Do you have any...

1546
02:08:28,077 --> 02:08:30,788
Any memories of your grandfather
before the accident?

1547
02:08:31,873 --> 02:08:33,624
Before your parents were killed?

1548
02:08:34,709 --> 02:08:37,295
Yeah. No, I don't know.

1549
02:08:38,462 --> 02:08:39,630
Why?

1550
02:08:42,383 --> 02:08:44,760
Because I don't think
he was your grandfather.

1551
02:09:04,238 --> 02:09:05,948
These are my parents.

1552
02:09:08,242 --> 02:09:09,577
My brother.

1553
02:09:11,412 --> 02:09:13,205
And this is you, isn't it?

1554
02:09:18,169 --> 02:09:21,839
The paper says the entire
family was killed.

1555
02:09:22,340 --> 02:09:25,676
The mother, the father, the boy, six.

1556
02:09:27,929 --> 02:09:30,139
And the girl, four.

1557
02:09:31,849 --> 02:09:34,936
But your name was never Saunière.

1558
02:09:35,019 --> 02:09:36,562
It's Saint-Clair.

1559
02:09:39,941 --> 02:09:42,276
It's one of the oldest families in France.

1560
02:09:42,944 --> 02:09:46,197
It's from a line of the Merovingian kings.

1561
02:09:55,289 --> 02:09:57,083
Royal blood.

1562
02:09:59,126 --> 02:10:00,711
I was so wrong.

1563
02:10:02,380 --> 02:10:06,676
Saunière didn't want you
to help guard the secret of the Holy Grail.

1564
02:10:08,386 --> 02:10:09,720
Sophie,

1565
02:10:12,223 --> 02:10:14,058
you are the secret.

1566
02:10:15,726 --> 02:10:17,645
You survived the accident.

1567
02:10:18,479 --> 02:10:21,232
If it even was an accident.

1568
02:10:21,315 --> 02:10:23,234
The Priory found out.

1569
02:10:23,901 --> 02:10:27,071
Somehow they concealed the fact
that you were alive.

1570
02:10:27,613 --> 02:10:30,574
They hid you with the Grand Master himself,

1571
02:10:31,492 --> 02:10:33,452
who raised you as his own.

1572
02:10:34,745 --> 02:10:36,539
According to all of this,

1573
02:10:37,999 --> 02:10:39,750
Princess Sophie,

1574
02:10:43,462 --> 02:10:45,089
you are the heir.

1575
02:10:47,133 --> 02:10:49,218
The end of the bloodline.

1576
02:10:50,803 --> 02:10:53,848
You are the last living descendent

1577
02:10:55,182 --> 02:10:57,018
of Jesus Christ.

1578
02:11:42,563 --> 02:11:43,939
What is this?

1579
02:11:45,983 --> 02:11:47,193
Sophie?

1580
02:11:50,446 --> 02:11:51,572
Who are you?

1581
02:11:51,655 --> 02:11:54,617
There have been many names.

1582
02:11:54,700 --> 02:11:56,327
The keepers.

1583
02:11:57,369 --> 02:11:59,163
Guardians.

1584
02:11:59,246 --> 02:12:01,791
The Priory of Sion.

1585
02:12:01,874 --> 02:12:06,921
But to you, Sophie, we are friends
of the man who raised you,

1586
02:12:07,588 --> 02:12:09,173
Jacques Saunière.

1587
02:12:11,592 --> 02:12:14,303
He would have wanted you to know

1588
02:12:14,386 --> 02:12:16,889
that he loved you very much.

1589
02:12:17,932 --> 02:12:22,019
And that the Priory are here
to protect you now

1590
02:12:22,103 --> 02:12:25,272
as they have always protected our family.

1591
02:12:27,858 --> 02:12:29,944
I gave you up once

1592
02:12:30,736 --> 02:12:33,531
knowing I might never see you again.

1593
02:12:37,243 --> 02:12:39,161
I'm your grandmother, Sophie.

1594
02:12:40,287 --> 02:12:43,707
I have prayed for this moment

1595
02:12:43,791 --> 02:12:45,668
for a very long time.

1596
02:12:47,294 --> 02:12:49,421
Welcome home, child.

1597
02:13:02,268 --> 02:13:03,477
Hey.

1598
02:13:13,821 --> 02:13:17,658
She has some things she wants to tell me.

1599
02:13:18,659 --> 02:13:21,036
About my family.

1600
02:13:27,543 --> 02:13:28,752
What will you do?

1601
02:13:29,920 --> 02:13:33,424
The legend will be revealed
when the heir reveals himself.

1602
02:13:34,258 --> 02:13:36,760
They just got the pronoun wrong.

1603
02:13:40,181 --> 02:13:41,807
She said when Saunière died

1604
02:13:41,891 --> 02:13:44,685
he took the location
of Mary's sarcophagus with him.

1605
02:13:44,768 --> 02:13:49,398
So there's no way to empirically prove
that I am related to her.

1606
02:13:52,151 --> 02:13:54,111
What would you do, Robert?

1607
02:13:55,070 --> 02:13:57,281
Okay, maybe there is no proof.

1608
02:13:57,364 --> 02:13:59,533
Maybe the Grail is lost forever.

1609
02:13:59,617 --> 02:14:03,329
But, Sophie, the only thing that matters
is what you believe.

1610
02:14:04,747 --> 02:14:07,875
History shows us
Jesus was an extraordinary man.

1611
02:14:07,958 --> 02:14:09,960
A human inspiration. That's it.

1612
02:14:10,836 --> 02:14:13,547
That's all the evidence has ever proved.

1613
02:14:15,007 --> 02:14:16,133
But...

1614
02:14:17,092 --> 02:14:18,969
When I was a boy...

1615
02:14:21,305 --> 02:14:25,184
When I was down in that well
Teabing told you about,

1616
02:14:28,520 --> 02:14:30,981
I thought I was going to die, Sophie.

1617
02:14:33,108 --> 02:14:35,236
What I did,

1618
02:14:35,319 --> 02:14:36,695
I prayed.

1619
02:14:38,030 --> 02:14:39,615
I prayed

1620
02:14:39,698 --> 02:14:42,660
to Jesus to keep me alive,

1621
02:14:42,743 --> 02:14:44,286
so I could see my parents again,

1622
02:14:44,370 --> 02:14:46,455
so I could go to school again,

1623
02:14:47,498 --> 02:14:49,750
so I could play with my dog.

1624
02:14:51,126 --> 02:14:54,129
Sometimes I wonder
if I wasn't alone down there.

1625
02:14:56,340 --> 02:14:59,176
Why does it have to be human or divine?

1626
02:14:59,260 --> 02:15:01,178
Maybe human is divine.

1627
02:15:02,471 --> 02:15:04,139
Why couldn't Jesus have been a father

1628
02:15:04,223 --> 02:15:07,017
and still been capable
of all those miracles?

1629
02:15:07,685 --> 02:15:10,479
Like turning water into wine?

1630
02:15:10,562 --> 02:15:13,691
Well, who knows? His blood is your blood.

1631
02:15:14,525 --> 02:15:17,611
Maybe that junkie in the park
will never touch a drug again.

1632
02:15:18,195 --> 02:15:21,323
Maybe you healed my phobia with your hands.

1633
02:15:21,407 --> 02:15:24,410
And maybe you're a knight on a Grail quest.

1634
02:15:27,246 --> 02:15:29,790
Well, here's the question.

1635
02:15:30,666 --> 02:15:33,377
A living descendent of Jesus Christ,

1636
02:15:34,920 --> 02:15:37,464
would she destroy faith?

1637
02:15:38,007 --> 02:15:40,884
Or would she renew it?

1638
02:15:43,554 --> 02:15:46,724
So again I say,
what matters is what you believe.

1639
02:15:49,059 --> 02:15:50,352
Thank you.

1640
02:15:52,521 --> 02:15:53,731
For bringing me here.

1641
02:15:55,774 --> 02:15:58,277
For letting him choose you,

1642
02:15:59,153 --> 02:16:00,362
Sir Robert.

1643
02:16:10,622 --> 02:16:11,623
You take care.

1644
02:16:13,208 --> 02:16:14,335
Yes.

1645
02:16:38,942 --> 02:16:40,110
Hey.

1646
02:16:53,123 --> 02:16:54,124
Nope.

1647
02:16:55,459 --> 02:16:57,711
Maybe I'll do better with the wine.

1648
02:17:01,131 --> 02:17:02,508
Godspeed.

1649
02:18:01,400 --> 02:18:02,776
Bloodline.

1650
02:18:06,196 --> 02:18:07,531
Rose Line.

1651
02:18:14,329 --> 02:18:16,373
"Hides beneath the Rose."

1652
02:19:07,925 --> 02:19:11,512
"The Holy Grail 'neath
ancient Roslin waits.

1653
02:19:14,681 --> 02:19:18,101
"Adorned in masters' loving art, She lies.

1654
02:19:34,243 --> 02:19:37,871
"The blade and chalice
guarding o'er Her gates.

1655
02:20:17,327 --> 02:20:20,831
"She rests at last beneath starry skies."

